            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_ad.00757_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" place="top"><handShift rend="printed"/>The Sierra Grande Mining Company of Lake Valley, New
                Mexico.</note>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Transfer Office,</name>
                    <name type="place">18 Exchange Building.</name>
                    <name type="place">Philadelphia,</name>
                    <date when="1883-03-20">March 20th, 1883.</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <head type="main-authorial">Dividend No. 6.<ptr target="loc.05677_n1"/></head>

            <p>The Board of Directors have this day declared a dividend (Number 6) of one hundred
                thousand dollars ($100,000), being twenty-five cents per share, payable at the
                Transfer Office of the Company on and after April 2d, 1883, to the stockholders
                then of record. Transfer books close on March 24th, at 3 P.M., and reopen April 3d,
                at 10 A. M.</p>

            <closer> 
                <salute>By order</salute>
                <signed>Benjamin H. Shoemaker, President</signed>
                <signed>Attest:&#8212;Geo. L. Smedley, Sec.</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_ad.00756_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
